{
  "description": "A close-up shot of the hull of a large ship, likely a freighter or cargo vessel, painted in shades of gray and black. The word \"EXPRESS\" is visible in white lettering along the side. There are numerous markings and numbers painted on the hull, indicating draft measurements and other navigational details. A circular symbol resembling a recycling logo and the number 5 are prominently featured. The hull shows signs of wear and tear, including rust and streaks, suggesting it has been exposed to the elements. A dark, bulbous bow is visible, and a red waterline is at the very bottom of the frame. The overall impression is one of industrial strength and maritime travel.",
